text: Nizhneye Tukbayevo () is a rural locality (a village) in Duvan-Mechetlinsky Selsoviet, Mechetlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 227 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 39 km from Bolsheustyikinskoye, 7 km from Duvan-Mechetlino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mechetlinsky District
title: Nizhneye Tukbayevo
